    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-11T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-11T11:00:00-05:00" n="208"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d208">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 <gloss target="#t_EW1">E.
                    W.</gloss>/7–1145: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 208 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative on the Allied Commission on
                        Reparations</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PEW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pauley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d208fn1">Sent over the signature of <persName
                            corresp="#p_HWA2">Harriman</persName>. Sent to Washington; relayed to
                            <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName>, then at sea, in telegram
                        No. 14 of July 11 (file No. 740.00119 (Potsdam)/8–645).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-11T19:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 11, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2516. From <persName corresp="#p_PEW1">Pauley</persName> to <gloss
                        target="#t_SecState1">SecState</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Have received a copy of <persName corresp="#p_HWA2">Harriman</persName>’s
                    communication to <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d208fn2">See <ref target="#d189fn1">document No. 189,
                            footnote 1</ref>.</note> listing 6 items which it is indicated the
                    President may wish to raise for discussion at forthcoming meeting of the Big
                    Three. I am strongly of the opinion that the topic “reparations” should be added
                    to this agenda. Will appreciate your advising the President immediately of my
                    views.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
